# Wallet v1

## Get deposit address

```shell
curl "https://<%= config[:api_domain] %>/v1/wallet/depositAddress/:asset"
  -H "<%= config[:authorization_method] %>"
```

```javascript
const <%= config[:sdk_class_name] %> = require('<%= config[:sdk_name] %>');

let api = <%= config[:sdk_class_name] %>.authorize('<api_token>');
let deposit_address = api.depositAddress("{asset}");
```

> The above command returns JSON structured like this:

```json
{
   "success":true,
   "result":{
      "asset": "ethereum",
      "address": "<eth_address>" 
   }
}
```

This endpoint retrieves the selected market status.

### HTTP Request

`GET https://<%= config[:api_domain] %>/v1/wallet/depositAddress/:asset`

### URL Parameters

Parameter | Description
--------- | -----------
asset | Cryptocurrency or token address
offset | Skip a number of elements as defined in offset
limit | Return a number of records not higher of limit

## create withdrawal request

```shell
curl "https://<%= config[:api_domain] %>/v1/wallet/withdrawal/:asset"
  -X PUT
  -d '{asset, amount, address, validation}'
  -H "<%= config[:authorization_method] %>"
```

```javascript
const <%= config[:sdk_class_name] %> = require('<%= config[:sdk_name] %>');

let api = <%= config[:sdk_class_name] %>.authorize('<api_token>');
let deposits = api.withdrawalRequest("{assets, amount, address, validation}");
```

> The above command returns JSON structured like this:

```json
{
   "success":true
}
```

This endpoint retrieves the selected market status.

### HTTP Request

`PUT https://<%= config[:api_domain] %>/v1/wallet/withdrawal/:asset`

### URL Parameters

Parameter | Description
--------- | -----------
asset | Asset to withdraw
amount | Amount to withdraw
address | Withdrawal address
validation.sfauth | Second Factor Authentication


